    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM ANCHORLOK SPRING BRAKE - BRAKE CHAMBER SERVICE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>BRAKE CHAMBER SERVICE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>REMOVE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always cage the compression spring with the release tool. Do not rely on air pressure to keep
                        spring compressed. Refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s04019_HL0401901.xml" xrefid="hl0401901">CAGING SPRING</hotlnk>. Failure to
                        cage the compression spring may result in forceful release of the compression spring which could
                        cause death, severe personal injury and/or property damage.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Block wheels to prevent vehicle from moving.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cage spring brake. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s04019_HL0401901.xml" xrefid="hl0401901">CAGING SPRING</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release air pressure to spring brake chamber and service brake chamber.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air line from spring brake chamber and service brake chamber. Tag lines for
                    proper reassembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401909">Figure 9</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401909" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401909" filename="../figg04/g0401909.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9. Air Connection Locations</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. SPRING BRAKE CHAMBER AIR PORT</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SERVICE BRAKE CHAMBER AIR PORT</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. NUT AND LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pin that fastens the spring brake push rod clevis to the slack adjuster.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removing from the vehicle, remove the two nuts and washers that fasten the double
                    diaphragm Anchorlok assembly to the mounting bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401909">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
